      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was just looking at some photos of deep space and it hit me... like, everything we do, every single thing, is just a tiny blip in a universe that doesn't care. in a few billion years the sun dies, then eventually everything just goes cold and dark forever. it makes everything feel so pointless. why do we even bother trying to survive if the end result is just nothingness?",
