    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, a \"rare and precious thing\" sounds nice but it feels like a cope. it doesnt change the math. any \"meaning\" we make up for ourselves is just a temporary illusion to keep us distracted from the fact that we're essentially just accidental biological machines on a rock that's eventually going to be vaporized. if the outcome is always zero, isn't all the effort just... unnecessary? it feels like we're just running on a treadmill that leads to a cliff.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
